The variable n is initialized to 100.
The code then prints the maximum value of the following two numbers:
1. int(n[0])-1+9*(len(n)-1)
2. sum([int(i) for i in n])

The first number is the sum of the digits of the first character of n and the sum of the digits of the remaining characters of n.
The second number is the sum of the digits of all the characters of n.
